    Parameters:
    - params (np.ndarray): Trainable coefficients used by the equation skeleton.
    """
    """Improved version of `equation_v1`.

    This version keeps the physically meaningful terms for nonlinear harmonic oscillator acceleration,
    and adds flexibility by including up to 12 parameters (MAX_NPARAMS), allowing for higher order or cross terms.

    Parameters:
        x0: time array
        x1: position array at time t
        x2: velocity array at time t
        params: array of parameters with length up to MAX_NPARAMS (12),
                where each param corresponds to a coefficient of a term below.

                Suggested param indexing:
                params[0]  = constant forcing term (c0)
                params[1]  = linear time coefficient (c_time)
                params[2]  = linear position coefficient (-k_lin)
                params[3]  = cubic position coefficient (-alpha_cu)
                params[4]  = linear velocity coefficient (-beta_damp)
                params[5]  = quadratic position coefficient (pos^2 term)
                params[6]  = quadratic velocity coefficient (vel^2 term)
                params[7]  = interaction term pos*vel
